            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJesus%20saw%20a%20terrible%20scene%20coming%20to%20Jerusalem%20in%20the%20not-too-distant%20future.%20He%20saw%20the%20Roman%20legions%20invading%20Jerusalem%20and%20completely%20destroying%20it%20in%20A.D.%2070.%20Josephus%2C%20the%20Jewish%20historian%2C%20reported%20that%20more%20than%20one%20million%20Jews%20died%20during%20this%20invasion%2C%20thousands%20of%20them%20by%20crucifixion%20outside%20of%20Jerusalem.%20The%20city%20was%20so%20leveled%20that%20a%20plow%20was%20pulled%20across%20it%20from%20side%20to%20side.%20David%20also%20foretold%20this%20horrible%20event%3A%20%22You%20have%20renounced%20your%20covenant%20with%20him%2C%20for%20you%20have%20thrown%20his%20crown%20in%20the%20dust.%20You%20have%20broken%20down%20the%20walls%20protecting%20him%20and%20laid%20in%20ruins%20every%20fort%20defending%20him%22%20(Psalm%2089%3A39-40).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20price%20for%20rejecting%20truth%20is%20high%2C%20and%20history%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20is%20strewn%20with%20the%20wreckage%20of%20civilizations%20that%20did%20just%20that.%20Joshua%20told%20the%20Israelites%20that%20if%20they%20forsook%20the%20Lord%2C%20He%20would%20turn%20against%20them%2C%20bring%20disaster%20on%20them%2C%20and%20make%20an%20end%20of%20them%20(Joshua%2024%3A20).%20God%20gives%20a%20season%20of%20opportunity%20to%20repent%2C%20but%20then%2C%20like%20a%20potter%20fashioning%20his%20pot%2C%20He%20destroys%20the%20vessel%20and%20makes%20another.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDetermine%20to%20be%20like%20Joshua%2C%20who%20said%2C%20%22But%20as%20for%20me%20and%20my%20family%2C%20we%20will%20serve%20the%20Lord%22%20(Joshua%2024%3A15).%20History%20will%20prove%20you%20right!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
